  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). This package conforms to the Minimal profile. An inline Requirement node (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-threshold) is referenced in the narrative and embedded in the validation evidence, but the top-level bindsRequirement link is intentionally absent per W-SI-02 test conditions.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou2-hemolysis-acceptable",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/hemolysis-experimental-mrl5"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/piv-velocity-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA pump benchmark",
      "description": "CFD velocity fields compared against FDA particle image velocimetry data for the generic centrifugal pump. Normalised RMS error 14.3% across 5 operating points. Requirement https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-threshold mandates hemolysis index below 0.01 g/100 mL; validation shows model under-predicts peak shear stress in gap regions by up to 22%, raising concern for absolute hemolysis predictions at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-index-mc",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo hemolysis index uncertainty quantification",
      "description": "1000-sample Monte Carlo propagation of inlet flow, fluid viscosity, and rotational speed uncertainty through the hemolysis power-law model. 95th-percentile hemolysis index exceeds the clinical threshold defined in the credibility requirement at 3 of 5 operating points. Confidence in absolute prediction remains insufficient at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — three-level GCI analysis",
      "description": "Grid convergence index study performed on coarse (2.1M cells), medium (6.4M cells), and fine (18.7M cells) meshes. GCI for hemolysis index between medium and fine meshes is 8.7%, exceeding the 3% threshold required at MRL 5. Discretization error remains a credibility gap."
    }
  ],
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with regression test suite covering hemolysis model; documented QA plan per MRL 5 requirements.",
      "rationale": "Solver is version-controlled and regression tests exist for core fluid equations, but the hemolysis power-law sub-model lacks dedicated regression coverage. QA plan does not address uncertainty propagation through the damage accumulation integral. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent analytical benchmark for all governing equations including hemolysis transport.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to Navier-Stokes equations only. Hemolysis scalar transport equation and power-law source term have not been verified against analytical solutions. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI below 3% for hemolysis index QoI on production mesh; Richardson extrapolation reported.",
      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study completed. GCI for hemolysis index is 8.7% between medium and fine meshes, exceeding the 3% threshold. Computational cost prevents further refinement. Richardson extrapolation performed but extrapolated value still exceeds clinical threshold at two operating points. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate all 5 COU operating points including fluid temperature, hematocrit, and rotational speed within specified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Four of five COU operating points are replicated in the experimental dataset. The fifth (maximum flow, maximum speed) was not tested due to pump cavitation risk in the test rig. Hematocrit controlled within ±2% for tested points. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalised RMSE) below 5% for hemolysis index across all tested operating points; statistical equivalence test performed.",
      "rationale": "Normalised RMSE for hemolysis index is 18.6% across four tested operating points. No statistical equivalence test performed. Peak discrepancy occurs in the blade trailing-edge region where shear stress is highest. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs directly correspond to the hemolysis index used in the submission decision; no surrogate metrics used.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) is used as both the validation QoI and the submission decision metric. However, the experimental NIH is measured via plasma-free haemoglobin assay whereas the CFD QoI is the power-law integral — a known model-form gap. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating envelope as the COU; no geometric scaling applied.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which differs from the proprietary VAD geometry in blade count and volute design. Geometric similarity is partial; Reynolds number matching is maintained but tip clearance ratio differs by 15%. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residuals below 1e-6 for all equations; floating-point round-off analysis documented for hemolysis accumulation integral.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored but residual thresholds not formally documented for the hemolysis scalar equation. Round-off analysis for the damage accumulation integral over long particle trajectories has not been performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup by qualified analyst; documented checklist for boundary condition assignment and material property entry.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation inputs was performed. Boundary condition assignments and material property entries were set by the same analyst who developed the model. Use error assessment not completed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selected based on published benchmark evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices; sensitivity to model form documented.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without benchmark justification for rotating blood-contacting geometries. Hemolysis power-law exponents (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) are known to over-predict hemolysis at low shear exposures. No model-form sensitivity study performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary conditions characterised with documented uncertainty distributions; Monte Carlo propagation covers all influential inputs.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo propagation performed for inlet flow rate, viscosity, and rotational speed. Blood viscosity modelled as Newtonian; non-Newtonian shear-thinning effects not included in uncertainty analysis. Hematocrit variability not propagated. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum three independent pump specimens tested; batch-to-batch variability in surface finish characterised and included in uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "All experimental data collected from a single pump specimen. Batch-to-batch variability in impeller surface finish, which affects near-wall shear stress and hemolysis, has not been characterised. Single-specimen testing is insufficient at MRL 5. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency analysis demonstrating that validation test inputs bound or match COU inputs for all parameters influencing hemolysis; documented parameter mapping table.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency analysis performed. Validation test used bovine blood at 37°C; COU involves human blood with patient-specific hematocrit variation. Parameter mapping between validation and COU inputs has not been documented. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    }
