    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 credibility factors under the Minimal profile submission. Despite multiple factors showing achieved levels below required levels, the submission is accepted under the Minimal profile pathway, which permits acceptance with documented gaps when the risk mitigation strategy is approved by the responsible authority. The inline requirement node (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-threshold) specifying an absolute hemolysis index threshold of 0.01 g/100 mL is referenced throughout the validation evidence and factor rationales. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification provides partial coverage of input uncertainty. The team acknowledges that six factors remain not-assessed and that the top-level package binding to the requirement IRI was not included in the submission index, consistent with Minimal profile obligations.",
